# Mark binary assets so git treats them as opaque in diff/merge and skips
# line-ending normalization. These files MUST NOT pass through a text / UTF-8
# round-trip (e.g. a find-and-replace that opens files with errors='replace'):
# that collapses non-UTF-8 bytes to U+FFFD (EF BF BD) and destroys the file
# (#1734). scripts/check_binary_integrity.py (pre-commit guard) catches such
# rewrites; this attribute is defense-in-depth and keeps diffs readable.
src/frontend/assets/**/*.ttf binary
src/frontend/assets/**/*.wasm binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.ico   binary
*.gif   binary
*.icns  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
